sentences: Martha Bass (March 7, 1921 – September 21, 1998) was an American gospel singer.
With Mother Ford's teaching and a wealth of church singing experience under her belt, she left St. Louis in the early 1950s to travel with the great Clara Ward Singers, but left after one year.
With Mother Ford's teaching and a wealth of church singing experience under her belt, she left St. Louis in the early 1950s to travel with the great Clara Ward Singers, but left after one year.
In the 1960s her album, "I'm So Grateful", established her as a gospel singer of the first rank.
She was married to James Peaston (1914-1981).
